coaching practice in both the full and sevens versions of the game, this book encourages the reader to think critically about their own coaching practice and to consider innovative new approaches to player and coach development. It is essential reading for all students of sports coaching with an interest in rugby, and for any coach, manager or administrator looking to develop better programmes in coach education"--cProvided by publisher.  a16 0aRugby footballxCoaching.  aGV 945.75 L54 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035226123  aGV 945.75 L54 2015wLCc1i0162035226123lON_SHELFmUAAUGp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu1/28/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2012014152bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/233447224